  "description": "A ring homomorphism is a [function](../../../concepts/function/index.md) $phi : R \to S$ between [rings](./ring.md) that preserves both operations and the multiplicative identity: $phi(a + b) = phi(a) + phi(b)$, $phi(a cdot b) = phi(a) cdot phi(b)$, and $phi(1_R) = 1_S$.",
